COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 23, L.D. 10
1 HUMAN RIGHTS COMMISSION, MAINE
2 Human Rights Commission - Regulation 0150
3 Initiative: Establishes a part-time Maine Human Rights Investigator position effective
4 October 1, 2025 and provides funding for related All Other costs.
5 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
6 POSITIONS - LEGISLATIVE COUNT 0.500 0.500
7 Personal Services $49,225 $52,064
8 All Other $5,763 $5,763
9 __________ __________
10 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $54,988 $57,827
115 '
12 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
13 number to read consecutively.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment limits the scope of the bill to the prohibition of discrimination in
1166 employment, education and extensions of credit on the basis of an individual's political
1177 activities, instead of political affiliation, including running for office, campaigning for a
1188 candidate for public office or fundraising for the benefit of a candidate, political party or
1199 political advocacy group.
2200 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2211 (See attached)
