14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment limits the scope of the bill to the prohibition of discrimination in
1166 employment, education and extensions of credit on the basis of an individual's political
1177 activities, instead of political affiliation, including running for office, campaigning for a
1188 candidate for public office or fundraising for the benefit of a candidate, political party or
